## Relay-G9 Bring-In Tool enables agents to hand off mid-conversation with structured context transfer
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:backend
**Depends on:** AgentConfig-G1, Chat-G6

- [ ] `bring_in` tool available to assistant (Nicole) during chat, accepting target profession and reason
- [ ] Tool switches `session.active_profession` and injects handoff note into chat history before next agent's turn
- [ ] Handoff note includes: classification, summary of understanding, warnings, and context pointers
- [ ] Next agent starts with its own system prompt + full conversation history + handoff note (no repeated questions)
- [ ] Frontend shows handoff event in chat (e.g., "Nicole brought in Isaac" with reason)
- [ ] Profession `allowed_tools` enforcement — only professions that have `bring_in` in their tool list can invoke it
- [ ] Handoff restricted to professions listed in `handoff_to` (Nicole can hand off to advisor/coder, not arbitrary targets)
---

